'''Wilhelm Aarstad''' (15 January 1854 – ??) was a Norwegian politician for the [[Liberal Left Party]].
He was born at Aarstad in [[Egersund]] as a son of farmers. He was a first cousin of [[Søren Tobias Årstad]], and moved to [[Stavanger]] to be a merchant like Søren's side of the family.<ref name=nsd>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.uib.no/polsys/index.cfm?urlname=storting&lan=&MenuItem=N1_1&ChildItem=&State=collapse&UttakNr=33&person=10039|title=Wilhelm Aarstad|publisher=Norwegian Social Science Data Services (NSD)|language=Norwegian|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref>
He was elected to Stavanger city council, and in [[Norwegian parliamentary election, 1909|1909]] to the [[Parliament of Norway]] as a deputy representative. He was the running mate of [[Jonas Schanche Kielland (born 1863)|Jonas Schanche Kielland]], and met in his place in parliamentary session in both 1911 and 1912.<ref name=nsd/>
